result.execSummary:
All charges against Laquette A Cain Allison in this case have been dismissed. These charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Laquette A Cain Allison is presumed innocent.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

State's Petition to Dismiss
Status hearing on September 29, 2022 at 10:00 am.

9:28 AM Defendant Laquette A Cain Allison not in court.  Prosecuting attorney Kerra Stumbris in court for the State of Wisconsin. Atty Rachel Boaz appears on behalf of defendant. Atty Boaz indicates the defendant is currently in the State of Indiana having been extradited. State does not show any documentation that the Indiana warrant has been satisfied and therefore not willing to dismiss at this time. State will look into the matter. Court informs the State they can file Motion and proposed order to dismiss but will also set another hearing date for follow-up only. No hearing notice generated for defendant to appear on this matter.
Status hearing scheduled for September 29, 2022 at 10:00 am.

Status hearing on September 27, 2022 at 10:00 am.

10:13am Atty Rachel Boaz appears on behalf of Defendant. Defendant Laquette Cain Allison does not appear. Seth Reinhart appears under Student Practice Act under supervision of Matthew Nugent.  Counsel informs the court as to case 22CF176, the defendant has turned herself in to the custody of the State of Indiana.  State will not move to dismiss at this time and wishes to further confirm first that the defendant has turned herself in to Indiana.
Further proceedings on July 18, 2022 at 10:00 am.

1:55pm Case recalled, defendant now appears. Same appearances. Court withdraws warrant. State indicates the warrant is currently being reviewed by the Indiana governor. State requests the court grant a 60 day extension.  No objection by Atty Boaz. Further Proceedings set for  7/18/22 at 10:00am

State requests warrant be issued immediately. Court issues warrant and orders bail be forfeited.
